-- Ex-divs to take 3.39 points off FTSE 100 on Jan. 15
-- 
-- Mon Jan 13, 2014 05:36AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 13 (Reuters) - The following FTSE 100 <.FTSE> companies will go ex-dividend on Wednesday, after which investors will no longer qualify for the latest dividend payout.

According to Reuters calculations at current market prices, the effect of  the resulting adjustment to prices by market-makers would take 3.39 points off  the index. COMPANY   (RIC)DIVIDEND INDEX IMPACT (pence)   (points) Ashtead   <AHT.L>2.25 0.04  Imperial Tobacco  <IMT.L>   81.20 3.06  Next  <NXT.L>   50.00 0.29  Among FTSE 250 <.FTMC> companies going ex-dividend are:COMPANY  (RIC)   DIVIDEND   (pence)